    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Corbin Carroll** (85.94), whose matchup against Walker presents the day\u2019s most significant ceiling. With a favorable SP_xERA of 4.79 and an elite order slot (#2), **Corbin Carroll** is our primary engine for stolen base volume, supported by a 19% SP skill advantage. We are also leaning heavily into the platoon-heavy profiles of **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92). **Mickey Moniak** benefits from Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez\u2019s slow delivery, which keeps our stolen base aggressive-stance intact, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** exploits a massive 19% skill gap against Erick Fedde. **Josh Naylor** (71.88) rounds out our top tier, effectively neutralizing Lance McCullers Jr. despite a slight park penalty, as the middle-of-the-order run production expectations remain high.\n\nThe optimizer faced its toughest decision regarding the final UTIL and middle-infield slots, ultimately siding with **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (69.72) over **Seiya Suzuki** (50.78). While **Seiya Suzuki** posted a respectable score, he was held back by a tougher matchup against Braxton Ashcraft and a perceived lack of relative upside compared to the multi-category reliability **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** offers in a high-leverage spot against Nick Martinez. We are keeping **Trevor Story**, **Austin Riley**, and **Kyle Karros** on the pine; while they are serviceable, they lack the specific platoon or park-adjusted tailwinds required to displace our current starters. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given that nearly all our hitters are currently \"Lineup Pending.\" We are particularly monitoring the wind conditions for **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, as their 5% boost is contingent on prevailing patterns at the park, and any shift in the official lineups could compress these margins. Additionally, while we like the upside for **Giancarlo Stanton** (59.81), we are proceeding with caution as the reliance on Nick Martinez\u2019s inefficiency is our only path to production there. We remain balanced, but should any of these \"Lineup Pending\" statuses shift to lower-order placements, we are prepared to pivot to more efficient bench depth to protect our daily game caps.",
